- `equiv_then_know_same`: If two processes are equivalent, then an agent knows a proposition in one if and only if it knows it in the other.
- `not_in_call_then_invariant_resultSet`: If an agent is not involved in a call `C`, then its result set is unchanged by `C`.
- `local_is_known`: An agent knows its own value.
- `knowledge_of_secrets_is_preserved`: Knowledge of a secret is preserved under refinement.
- `know_your_own`: An agent knows its own value.

